      "content": "resting in the dirt... that's exactly it. but the thing is, there's no real rest when people are still looking at you, still judging you, even if they don't say it. it just feels like a cycle of shame that never actually stops. why is the only \"peace\" presented as just waiting for everything to finally go quiet? it feels like there's no version of the future where I'm not just a broken version of who I used to be.",
